other_tests.findings: Confirmed the presence of 55 CAG trinucleotide repeats on chromosome 4, indicative of Huntington's disease.
Mild atrophy of the bilateral nucleus caudatus and corpus striatum relative to normal features for her age.
Atrophy of the striatum and enlargement of the frontal horns, characteristic findings of Huntington's Disease. No increased intensity observed in the caudate nucleus and putamen.
